			<ns0:name>bradnelson@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/bradnelson@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">While I suppose -Werror is less common amongst open source projects in general (see 
regression to the mean... :-), I don't think that's a good reason not to aspire to it. 
For instance you'll notice throughout chromium's gyp file's the flag: chromium_code, 
which indirectly turns on -Wall + -Werror, with the intention that code we have 
oversight on be -Werror clean. If there are compilers with better errors, we should 
start using them and add more builders. That being said, drilling a flag to disable -
Werror globally sounds like a reasonable option as a porting aid.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-05-20T18:43:46.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-05-20T18:43:46.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates>
